div.div: This would mean after the plot is saved we can then copy the data into a buffer using an io.BytesIO object as a memory buffer to save the image file to after reading from \tmp. It would then be safe to drop the image from \tmp and then base64encode the image from the memory buffer into memory before passing into the HTML template. The memory buffers and stored encodings should be dropped on function exit. It may be too intensive to run a cache, so we will calculate each time at the cost of responsiveness.
